General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 percent (50%) of the service is as a law enforcement officer as herein defined
2 or as a probation/parole officer as defined in G.S. 135-1(17a).officer.
3 (3) Law enforcement officer. – As defined in either G.S. 135-1 or
4 G.S. 143-166.30(a).
5 (4) Officer. – A law enforcement officer.
6 (5) Probation/parole officer. – As defined in G.S. 135-1.
7 (b1) Eligibility for Allowance and Calculation of Allowance Amount. – To be eligible for
8 an allowance under this section, an officer is required to meet one of the following sets of criteria
9 that shall also determine the allowance amount:
10 (1) For officers meeting all of the following criteria, the annual special separation
11 allowance to be paid is equal to eighty-five hundredths percent (0.85%) of the
12 annual base rate of compensation most recently applicable to the officer for
13 each year of that officer's creditable service:
14 a. The officer (i) has completed 30 or more years of creditable service or
15 (ii) is 55 years of age or older and completed five or more years of
16 creditable service.
17 b. The officer is less than 62 years of age.
18 c. The officer has completed at least five years of continuous service as
19 a law enforcement officer immediately preceding the officer's service
20 retirement. Any break in this required continuous service that is a
21 result of disability retirement or disability salary continuation benefits
22 shall not adversely affect an officer's qualification to receive an
23 allowance under this subdivision so long as the officer returned to
24 service within 45 days after the disability benefits had ceased and is
25 otherwise qualified to receive the allowance.
26 (2) For officers meeting all of the following criteria, the annual special separation
27 allowance to be paid is equal to eighty-five hundredths percent (0.85%) of the
28 annual equivalent of the base rate of compensation at the time the officer
29 attained 30 years of service multiplied by 30:
30 a. The officer has completed 30 or more years of creditable service prior
31 to attaining 62 years of age.
32 b. The officer has completed at least five years of continuous service as
33 a law enforcement officer immediately preceding the officer's service
34 retirement. Any break in this required continuous service that is a
35 result of disability retirement or disability salary continuation benefits
36 shall not adversely affect an officer's qualification to receive an
37 allowance under this subdivision so long as the officer returned to
38 service within 45 days after the disability benefits had ceased and is
39 otherwise qualified to receive the allowance.
40 If an officer meets all of the criteria under each subdivision of this subsection, then the
41 employer making the allowance payments shall allow the officer to choose which of the two
42 calculation formulas to use for that officer's allowance. This election by the officer is a one-time,
43 irrevocable election and shall be made prior to the first allowance payment. If no election is made
44 by the officer, then the calculation amount under subdivision (2) of this subsection shall be used.
45 (c) Cessation of Payment. – Payment of the allowance to a retired officer under the
46 provisions of this section shall cease at the first of:occurrence of one of the following:
47 (1) The death of the officer;officer.
48 (2) The last day of the month in which either of the following applies:
49 a. If the officer is receiving an allowance in an amount determined under
50 subdivision (b1)(1) of this section, the officer attains 62 years of age;
51 orage.
