1 b. If the officer is receiving an allowance in an amount determined under
2 subdivision (b1)(2) of this section, there has been a period of receiving
3 the allowance that is equivalent to the total of 62 years minus the age
4 at which the officer first completed 30 years of creditable service.
5 (3) The first day of reemployment by any State department, agency, or institution,
6 except that this subdivision does not apply to an officer returning to State
7 employment in a position exempt from the North Carolina Human Resources
8 Act in an agency other than the agency from which that officer retired.
9 (d) Impact of Other Benefits or Actions. – This section does not affect the benefits to
10 which an individual may be entitled from State, federal, or private retirement systems. The
11 benefits payable under this section shall not be subject to any increases in salary or retirement
12 allowances that may be authorized by the General Assembly for employees of the State or retired
13 employees of the State.
14 (e) Eligibility Determinations. – The head of each State department, agency, or institution
15 shall determine the eligibility of employees for the benefits provided herein.under this section.
16 (f) Transfer of Funds. – The Director of the Budget may authorize from time to time the
17 transfer of funds within the budgets of each State department, agency, or institution necessary to
18 carry out the purposes of this Article. section. These funds shall be taken from those funds
19 appropriated to the department, agency, or institution for salaries and related fringe benefits.
20 (g) Responsibility for Payment. – The head of each State department, agency, or
21 institution shall make the payments set forth in subsection (a) this section to those persons
22 certified under subsection (e) of this section from funds available under subsection (f).(f) of this
23 section."
24 SECTION 2. G.S. 143-166.42 reads as rewritten:
25 "§ 143-166.42. Special separation allowances allowance options for local law enforcement
26 officers.
27 (a) Annual Special Separation Allowance. – On and after January 1, 1987, every sworn
28 law enforcement officer as defined by G.S. 128-21(11d) or G.S. 143-166.50(a)(3) employed by
29 a local government employer who qualifies under this section shall receive, receive an annual
30 special separation allowance beginning in the month in which the officer retires on a basic service
31 retirement under the provisions of G.S. 128-27(a), an annual separation allowance equal to
32 eighty-five hundredths percent (0.85%) of the annual equivalent of the base rate of compensation
33 most recently applicable to the officer for each year of creditable service. G.S. 128-27(a). The
34 allowance shall be paid in equal installments on the payroll frequency used by the employer. To
35 qualify for the allowance, the officer shall:
36 (1) Have (i) completed 30 or more years of creditable service or (ii) have attained
37 55 years of age and completed five or more years of creditable service; and
38 (2) Not have attained 62 years of age; and
39 (3) Have completed at least five years of continuous service as a law enforcement
40 officer as herein defined immediately preceding a service retirement. Any
41 break in the continuous service required by this subsection because of
42 disability retirement or disability salary continuation benefits shall not
43 adversely affect an officer's qualification to receive the allowance, provided
44 the officer returns to service within 45 days after the disability benefits cease
45 and is otherwise qualified to receive the allowance.employer from which the
46 officer retired.
